<P><STRONG>Things to try out:</STRONG>=20
<OL>
  <LI>Compile and run the program.&nbsp; Test out the keyboard =
controls.&nbsp;=20
  When it first starts, aliasing causes the planet to appear to not be =
rotating,=20
  but instead always keeping the same face to the sun.&nbsp;&nbsp; Slow =
down the=20
  animation (arrow keys) to see the "true" motion.&nbsp; Figure out how =
the=20
  animation code works (refer to chapter 2 of the above-mentioned book). =

  <LI>If you didn't already do this with the <STRONG>SimpleAnim</STRONG> =

  program, try changing the program to use single buffering, and observe =
the=20
  results.=20
  <LI>Build a more complicated solar system, by doing the solar system =
exercise=20
  from chapter 2 of the book (page XXX).=20
  <LI>The perspective view is set up poorly for some situations.&nbsp; =
Try, for=20
  instance, making a tall skinny window; note that the solar system is =
no longer=20
  fully visible. &nbsp; Rewrite the <STRONG>ResizeWindow</STRONG> =
routine to fix=20
  this problem. </LI></OL></BODY></HTML>
